}} '''维多利亚音乐厅惨案'''，1883年6月16日发生于英格兰[[桑德兰|桑德兰]]的维多利亚音乐厅，共有183名儿童死亡。 

== 惨案 ==
1883年6月16日，费伊夫妇在维多利亚音乐厅办了一场面向儿童的[[綜藝節目|综艺节目]]，观众内估计有1100名儿童。<ref name="vic">{{Cite web|title=Sunderland's Victoria Hall Stampede|url=http://www.north-country.co.uk/victoria.htm|accessdate=2007-01-27|work=North Country Web|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070108182434/http://www.north-country.co.uk/victoria.htm|archivedate=2007-01-08}}</ref><ref name="vicdisaster">{{Cite web|title=Children's deaths that shocked the world|url=http://www.sunderlandecho.com/daily/Children39s-deaths-that-shocked-the.4183073.jp|accessdate=2008-06-13|author=Sarah Stoner|year=2008|work=Sunderland Echo|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080621023341/https://www.sunderlandecho.com/daily/Children39s-deaths-that-shocked-the.4183073.jp|archivedate=2008-06-21}}</ref>演出结束时，费伊夫妇宣布门票编号为特定数字的儿童在出口处可以获得奖品。同时，演员开始从舞台上向[[劇場_(建築)|剧场]]的孩子们分发礼物。因为担心错过奖励，许多儿童涌向通往楼下的楼梯。<ref>{{Cite web|title=Victims of the Victoria Hall Calamity|url=http://www.genuki.org.uk/big/eng/DUR/Sunderland/VictoriaHall.html|accessdate=2007-01-27|work=Genuki}}</ref>然而，在楼梯的尽头，门是向内打开的，并用螺栓固定住，留出的间隙一次只能让一个儿童通过。这种做法可能是方便对门票进行有序检查。<ref name="vic2">{{Cite magazine|title=The Victoria Hall Disaster 1883|url=http://www.sunderland.gov.uk/CHttpHandler.ashx?id=6964&p=0|format=PDF|publisher=Sunderland City Council|issue=5|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130615160022/http://www.sunderland.gov.uk/CHttpHandler.ashx?id=6964&p=0|archive-date=2013-06-15|access-date=2013-10-18}}</ref>儿童从楼梯冲向门口，几乎没有成人陪同维持秩序，最终导致冲在前面的儿童被身后的人群挤压致死。 

音乐厅里的成年人意识到发生了什么事以后，他们冲到门前，但由于螺栓在儿童一侧，他们也无法把门完全打开。看门人Frederick Graham尝试一番未果，遂跑上另一个楼梯，从另一个出口将大约600名儿童转移到安全地带。<ref name="vic">{{Cite web|title=Sunderland's Victoria Hall Stampede|url=http://www.north-country.co.uk/victoria.htm|accessdate=2007-01-27|work=North Country Web|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070108182434/http://www.north-country.co.uk/victoria.htm|archivedate=2007-01-08}}</ref>同时，其他成年人从窄缝中将孩子们一一拉出，最后一名男子将门从铰链上拧下。

== 后续 ==
[[File:Victoria_Hall_Memorial.png|左]]
事故造成183名3至14岁的儿童[[窒息|窒息]]死亡，是英国历史上同类型事故中最严重的一场灾难。<ref name="vic2">{{Cite magazine|title=The Victoria Hall Disaster 1883|url=http://www.sunderland.gov.uk/CHttpHandler.ashx?id=6964&p=0|format=PDF|publisher=Sunderland City Council|issue=5|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130615160022/http://www.sunderland.gov.uk/CHttpHandler.ashx?id=6964&p=0|archive-date=2013-06-15|access-date=2013-10-18}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title=The Victoria Hall Disaster of 1883|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/dna/h2g2/A882173|accessdate=2007-05-26|date=2002-12-17|work=The Hitchhiker's Guide to the Galaxy: Earth Edition|publisher=BBC}}</ref>[[维多利亚_(英国女王)|维多利亚女王]]向死难者家属表示慰问，并为此次事件捐款。<ref>{{Cite web|title=Victoria Hall Disaster Toy Rocking Horse|url=http://www.bbc.co.uk/ahistoryoftheworld/objects/4gVnbOcJTOG0qJLYxnA9rw|accessdate=2018-06-15|publisher=BBC}}</ref>英国各地的捐款总额为5,000英镑，用于孩子们的葬礼和公园的纪念雕像。雕像雕刻的是一位悲伤的母亲抱着一个死去的孩子。后来，雕像被转移到Bishopwearmouth公墓，年久失修，遭到破坏。2002年，政府花63,000英镑对雕像进行了修复，移回了Mowbray公园。<ref name="vicdisaster">{{Cite web|title=Children's deaths that shocked the world|url=http://www.sunderlandecho.com/daily/Children39s-deaths-that-shocked-the.4183073.jp|accessdate=2008-06-13|author=Sarah Stoner|year=2008|work=Sunderland Echo|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080621023341/https://www.sunderlandecho.com/daily/Children39s-deaths-that-shocked-the.4183073.jp|archivedate=2008-06-21}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|date=2002-05-12|title=Toy Tragedy Children Honoured|work=BBC News|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/1/hi/england/1925815.stm|accessdate=2007-01-27}}</ref> 

此次事故引起了全国性的愤怒情绪，由此引发的调查导致政府立法对公共娱乐场所外开的[[緊急出口|紧急出口]]的最小数量作出规定，<ref name="vicdisaster">{{Cite web|title=Children's deaths that shocked the world|url=http://www.sunderlandecho.com/daily/Children39s-deaths-that-shocked-the.4183073.jp|accessdate=2008-06-13|author=Sarah Stoner|year=2008|work=Sunderland Echo|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080621023341/https://www.sunderlandecho.com/daily/Children39s-deaths-that-shocked-the.4183073.jp|archivedate=2008-06-21}}</ref>也导致了[[推杆紧急门|推杆紧急门]]的发明。<ref>{{Cite web|title=183 Children Died in a Stampede for Toys in 1883|url=http://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/183-children-died-in-a-stampede-for-toys-in-1883-173637/|accessdate=2016-12-04|author=Eveleth|date=2013-08-19|first=Rose|work=Smithsonian}}</ref>这项法律今天仍然有效。没有人因这场事故而受到起诉，负责栓门的人也未得到确认。维多利亚音樂厅一直使用到[[第二次世界大战|二战]]时的1941年，最后被[[降落伞炸弹|降落伞炸弹]]炸毁。<ref>{{Cite book|last=Talbot|first=Bryan|title=[[Alice_in_Sunderland|Alice in Sunderland: An Entertainment]]|publisher=Jonathon Cape|year=2007|isbn=0-224-08076-8|location=London|pages=58–60|authorlink=Bryan Talbot}}</ref>

